we use camelBack notation for enum variables, variables and methods.
CamelCase for classes, interfaces and enums
no fucking CAPS for anything.
a '{' never goes on a new line.
try to keep methods on a one page length.
use singletons for entry points
use libgdx provided classes and methods as much as possible.
comment your shit and use meaningful names for everything
try to limit your classes to a one-trick-pony type. layers of abstraction exist for a reason
try to think on how other people use your classes. encapsulation, final and abstract keywords do exist
use static with care.
more to come...
